<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That said, if you just=C2=A0<em>wanted=C2=A0</=
em>to have a liquidity crisis, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyMi8xMS8xNC=
90ZWNobm9sb2d5L2Z0eC1zYW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1jcnlwdG8tYmFua3J1cHRjeS5odG1s/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6dbaaf11" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> here=E2=80=99s one way to do it=
</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile, at a meeting with Alameda employees=
 on Wednesday, [Alameda CEO Caroline]=C2=A0Ellison explained what had cause=
d the collapse, according to a person familiar with the matter. Her voice s=
haking, she apologized, saying she had let the group down. Over recent mont=
hs, she said, Alameda had taken out loans and used the money to make ventur=
e capital investments, among other expenditures.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Around the time the crypto market crashed this=
 spring, Ms. Ellison explained, lenders moved to recall those loans, the pe=
rson familiar with the meeting said. But the funds that Alameda had spent w=
ere no longer easily available, so the company used FTX customer funds to m=
ake the payments.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yes, no, right, if you are a crypto hedge fund=
, and you take out short-term loans, and you use those loans to=C2=A0<em>ma=
ke venture capital investments</em>, then your loans will come due long bef=
ore the time horizon of your venture investments, and then I guess you=E2=
=80=99ll =E2=80=A6=C2=A0use customer money from your affiliated exchange to=
 repay the loans? What was the good way for this to go?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTQvZnR4LXMtYmFsYW5jZS1zaGVldC13YXMtYmFkP2NtcGlkPUJC=
RDExMTUyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGV=
yJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTExNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cCfe14315e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  talked extensively yesterday</a> about the crisis=
 at FTX. The basic situation is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">FTX owes customers something like $9 =
billion.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Its balance sheet =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0really the combined balance sheet of FTX, Alameda=C2=A0and various=
 affiliates =E2=80=94=C2=A0consists mostly of cobwebs and magic beans.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Where did the money go?</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CInto venture investments=E2=80=9D is =
only a very partial answer, since those venture investments=C2=A0<em>are=C2=
=A0</em>on <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/2970759=
0.273527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMGMyYTU1YjYtZDM0Yy00Njg1LThhOG=
QtM2M5NjI4ZjFmMTg1/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB94f49264" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> the balance =
sheet</a>, at cost, totaling about $3 billion. I speculated on some other p=
ossibilities, with the simplest being something like =E2=80=9CAlameda made =
leveraged bets on cryptocurrencies, lost money in volatile crypto markets, =
and took FTX customer money to pay back its loans.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But this is all very speculative and there are=
 not a lot of facts available. You can find other explanations online, and =
I would like to link to some of them here, with heavy caveats.=C2=A0I don=
=E2=80=99t want to vouch for these analyses, because they are speculative a=
nd sometimes anonymous and the facts remain murky. But I do want to summari=
ze them, because they are interesting and sort of rhyme with each other. He=
re is a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.2=
73527/aHR0cHM6Ly9taWxreWVnZ3MuY29tLz9wPTE3NQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB67e1b=
a70" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> blog post</a> from =E2=80=9CMilky Eggs=E2=80=9D on =E2=80=9CW=
hat happened at Alameda Research,=E2=80=9D and here are Twitter threads fro=
m <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.273527/=
aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9UZW5zYWlDYXBpdGFsL3N0YXR1cy8xNTkxODE0MTQwMTUwMDk=
xNzgw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB69de247e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Tensai Capital</a> and =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.273527/aH=
R0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS8weGRvdWcvc3RhdHVzLzE1OTExNjE5ODc1NDcxNjg3Njg/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cBdf549386" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Doug Colkitt</a>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Basically if you read these accounts, not nece=
ssarily focusing too much on specific hard-to-verify claims, the sense you =
will get is something like:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Alameda Research did a ton of trading=
 on FTX. If you =E2=80=94=C2=A0a regular person or a crypto hedge fund =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0came to FTX to trade, there=E2=80=99s a good chance you were tr=
ading against Alameda.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Alameda was=
 not very good at trading. If you traded against Alameda on FTX, there=E2=
=80=99s a good chance you made money.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What exactly No. 2 means can vary. It could me=
an, like, on a market microstructure level, Alameda did not have the best v=
iew of crypto prices, and so sophisticated high-frequency crypto traders co=
uld reliably make money trading against it. (<a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS8weGRv=
dWcvc3RhdHVzLzE1OTExNjIxMTMzMzAxMzkxMzY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3dad6a23" =
itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"c=
olor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; =
border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color:=
 #ccc;">Colkitt</a>: =E2=80=9CCrypto trading firms had the illusion they we=
re skilled. Instead all they were doing was winning against the Washington =
Generals.=E2=80=9D) But it could also be a story about FTX=E2=80=99s liquid=
ation engine: Customers could make levered bets on cryptocurrencies on FTX =
and be automatically liquidated if the bets moved against them, and this li=
quidation seems to have consisted largely of Alameda buying their positions=
. This was a good experience for customers =E2=80=94=C2=A0it made betting o=
n FTX more predictable and less risky =E2=80=94=C2=A0and possibly good for =
Alameda, if it bought stuff that went down and then the stuff went up again=
. But when the Luna token collapsed earlier this year, Alameda would (on th=
is theory) have been buying tons of Luna all the way down, leaving it with =
a huge stash of worthless Luna and a big loss.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But never mind the details; the point of this =
theory=C2=A0is that FTX offered a very good customer experience to traders =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0if you traded on FTX, you made money =E2=80=94=C2=A0at the e=
xpense of Alameda constantly losing money to those traders. And when money =
got too tight at Alameda, the theory goes, FTX dipped into customer money t=
o keep Alameda afloat.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you believe some form of this theory, it is=
 a mixed bag. On the one hand, doesn=E2=80=99t it sound sort of nice? FTX w=
asn=E2=80=99t dipping into customer money to make wild speculative bets, or=
 to pay for its executives=E2=80=99 lifestyles. It was just really committe=
d to providing a good customer experience, and that is expensive, and so it=
 ended up running at a loss, and unfortunately it dipped into customer mone=
y to subsidize that loss. The other good news, on this theory, is that the =
answer to the question =E2=80=9Cwhere did the money go=E2=80=9D would be =
=E2=80=9Cmostly back to the customers=E2=80=9D: Some customers=E2=80=99 fun=
ds were lost, but they went back to other customers in the form of trading =
gains.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand,=C2=A0there is a technical n=
ame, in law and finance, for this sort of thing. It is a bad name. When you=
 have a business that takes money from some customers and uses it to genera=
te trading gains for other customers, that=E2=80=99s just, I am sorry, a Po=
nzi scheme. I am not sure it=E2=80=99s worse than any other explanation of =
what happened =E2=80=94=C2=A0in any case, the customer money is missing! =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0but it=E2=80=99s not=C2=A0<em>good</em>.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In other FTX news, the Wall Street Journal <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9mdHgtZm91bmRlci1zYW0tYmFua21hbi1mcmllZC1h=
dHRlbXB0cy10by1yYWlzZS1mcmVzaC1jYXNoLWRlc3BpdGUtYmFua3J1cHRjeS0xMTY2ODUyMDU=
3Mz9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3Mx/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB73601bef" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> repor=
ts that</a> =E2=80=9CFTX filed for bankruptcy last week, but the cryptocurr=
ency exchange=E2=80=99s founder still thinks that he can raise enough money=
 to make users whole, according to people familiar with the matter. Mr. Ban=
kman-Fried, alongside a few remaining employees, spent the past weekend cal=
ling around in search of commitments from investors to plug a shortfall of =
up to $8 billion in the hopes of repaying FTX=E2=80=99s customers, the peop=
le said.=E2=80=9D I really do not understand what investors would be gettin=
g for their $8 billion but I guess I hope it works? I hope he=E2=80=99s cal=
ling the Binance fund.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And FTX=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2Nvbn=
RlbnQvMWRmZTkwM2ItZDE2NC00ZDdlLWE0Y2UtMTc1M2NkYjYyN2M5/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cBa045d84e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> chaotic bankruptcy filing</a> means we still don=E2=
=80=99t have much in the way of information from FTX about what happened, t=
hough that is starting to change a little bit. Here is <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYn=
dieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JUbEM5N2FVWExGTS92MA/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB18b9b26f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> a motion</a> filed by FTX in its bank=
ruptcy case yesterday; it isn=E2=80=99t very interesting, honestly, but it =
does have this short version of the collapse:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">FTX faced a severe liquidity crisi=
s that necessitated the filing of these cases on an emergency basis last Fr=
iday. Questions arose about Ml. Bankman-Fried's leadership and the handling=
 of FTX's complex array of assets and businesses under his direction. As th=
e situation became increasingly dire, Sullivan &amp; Cromwell and =C3=83lva=
rez &amp; Marsal North America, LLC ("Alvarez &amp; Marsal") were engaged t=
o provide restructuring advice and services to FTX. At approximately 4:30 a=
.m. on Friday, November 11, after consultation with his own legal counsel, =
Mr. Bankman-Fried ultimately agreed to step aside, resulting in the appoint=
ment of John J. Ray III, an experienced restructuring executive, as Chief E=
xecutive Officer.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And the New York Times reports that Bankman-Fr=
ied =E2=80=9Chas also found other ways to occupy his time in recent days, p=
laying the video game Storybook Brawl, though less than he usually does,=E2=
=80=9D and =E2=80=A6=C2=A0doing weird tweets?</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Shortly before the interview, Mr. Bankman-Frie=
d had posted a cryptic tweet: the word =E2=80=9CWhat.=E2=80=9D Then he had =
tweeted the letter H. Asked to explain, Mr. Bankman-Fried said he planned t=
o post the letter A and then the letter P. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s going to b=
e more than one word,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m making it up a=
s I go.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So he was planning a series of cryptic tweets?=
 =E2=80=9CSomething like that.=E2=80=9D<br /><br />But why? =E2=80=9CI don=
=E2=80=99t know,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m improvising. I thin=
k it=E2=80=99s time.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">By noon today he got through =E2=80=9CWhat H-A=
-P-P-E-N-E-D,=E2=80=9D followed by a legal disclaimer and =E2=80=9CI'll get=
