<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If I were a young person looking for a place t=
o start a career in finance, one niche that I might consider is ESG Consult=
ant But Evil. A lot of big companies and investors these days are looking f=
or ways to improve their environmental, social and governance ratings, and =
a lot of them will go to various sorts of ESG consultants who will tell the=
m how to cut emissions or whatever. But some of them will go to ESG Consult=
ants But Evil, who will sort of sneak in through the back door and say =E2=
=80=9Chey I=E2=80=99ve got some=C2=A0carbon credits that fell off a truck, =
I=E2=80=99ll sell =E2=80=99em to you for 20 cents on the dollar.=E2=80=9D L=
ots of people want to go into ESG to save the world, so that is a competiti=
ve business. Getting into ESG for the financial engineering seems pretty in=
teresting and possibly less crowded.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Possibly more crowded though. Here are <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDkvdG9wLXBlcmZvcm1p=
bmctc2luZ2Fwb3JlLXN0b2NrLXdpdGgtdGVtYXNlay1iYWNraW5nLWlzLWFjY3VzZWQtb2YtZ3J=
lZW53YXNoaW5nP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMTUyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdX=
RtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTExNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzd=
HVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa47a1bf8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Bloomberg=E2=80=99s=C2=
=A0Sheryl Tian Tong Lee and Stephen Stapczynski</a>=C2=A0last week:=C2=A0</=
p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One of Singapore=E2=80=99s best-performing sto=
cks this year =E2=80=94=C2=A0an energy company backed by state investor=C2=
=A0Temasek Holdings Pte=C2=A0=E2=80=94 is=C2=A0under fire for trying to avo=
id higher interest payments to bondholders that kick in if the company fail=
s to meet=C2=A0emissions targets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In order to reduce its official carbon footpri=
nt,=C2=A0Sembcorp Industries Ltd.=C2=A0sold two coal-fired power plants to =
an Omani group for $1.5 billion. The company told shareholders that the sal=
e would lower its=C2=A0greenhouse gas=C2=A0emissions intensity=C2=A0by 38%,=
 more than enough to dodge the penalties attached to the company=E2=80=99s=
=C2=A0sustainability-linked bonds.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the firm financed the sale=C2=A0=C2=A0of t=
he assets with a 15-year loan=C2=A0and retains =E2=80=9Csubstantial=E2=80=
=9D liabilities and =E2=80=9Coperational influence,=E2=80=9D over the busin=
ess, according to a report by=C2=A0Anthropocene Fixed Income Institute, a L=
ondon-based think tank. That effectively makes Sembcorp a shadow bank for t=
he coal industry, Anthropocene argues, and=C2=A0the carbon footprint of the=
 coal plants shouldn=E2=80=99t be removed until the loan is fully repaid.=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sembcorp, in which Temasek=C2=A0holds a 49% st=
ake, has two outstanding=C2=A0sustainability-linked bonds=C2=A0totaling S$9=
75 million ($697=C2=A0million).=C2=A0Under the performance targets, the com=
pany has to pay an extra 25 basis points in interest if it failed to meet t=
he emissions intensity targets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The sale of the coal plants is =E2=80=9Cpurely=
 a greenwashing exercise,=E2=80=9D said=C2=A0Kelvin Law, an associate profe=
ssor of accounting at Singapore=E2=80=99s Nanyang Technological University.=
 =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s the same facilities, same group of employees, same p=
olluting activities, just under a different name.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I=E2=80=99m sorry, I know I=E2=80=99m a monste=
r, but I love it so much? The point here is that =E2=80=9Ccarbon footprint=
=E2=80=9D is an=C2=A0<em>accounting regime</em>, a set of conventions. Cert=
ain sorts of companies =E2=80=94=C2=A0big public companies with ESG-focused=
 investors, big companies that borrow from big banks using sustainability-l=
inked bonds, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0are sensitive to carbon accounting. The mo=
re carbon emissions are on their carbon accounting statement, the worse off=
 they are. Other sorts of companies =E2=80=94=C2=A0Middle Eastern sovereign=
 wealth funds, Russian oligarchs, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0are less sensitive, o=
r insensitive, to carbon accounting. Nobody looks at their carbon accountin=
g statements, nobody cares, they can pollute as much as they want.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So if you are a carbon-sensitive company, you =
find a carbon-insensitive company, and you park your carbon on its balance =
sheet. And you pay it some fee for the service, which is presumably less th=
an you=E2=80=99re saving on your sustainability bonds or whatever. It is th=
e purest sort of financial engineering, transferring this abstract cost to =
the cheapest bearer of the cost.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Just! Imagine being=C2=A0the banker who shows =
up at the energy company that is trying to get rid of coal, and being like =
=E2=80=9CI have a way to get rid of your coal for you,=E2=80=9D and they ar=
e like =E2=80=9Cis it wind power,=E2=80=9D and you are like =E2=80=9Coh no,=
 we=E2=80=99re gonna get a novelty oversized fake mustache and glue it on t=
he front of your coal plants so we can pretend they=E2=80=99re someone else=
=E2=80=99s coal plants.=E2=80=9D ESG Consulting But Evil. It=E2=80=99s perf=
ect, I love it, no notes.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh, I can=E2=80=99t resist, one note. The trad=
e here is that you have someone for whom=C2=A0carbon emissions are expensiv=
e, and you arrange a trade to park its emissions with a counterparty who is=
 indifferent to emissions, for a fee.=C2=A0Great trade, fantastic, but you =
could do better. What you really want is a counterparty who wants to=C2=A0<=
em>increase its emissions</em>. You want a counterparty who will boast, lik=
e,=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cwe are on track to emit more carbon this year than we ever=
 have before, we are the world leaders in pollution,=E2=80=9D because it ge=
ts some economic=C2=A0<em>benefit=C2=A0</em>from increasing emissions.=C2=
=A0Ideally you want one side of the trade who will=C2=A0<em>pay to get rid =
of emissions</em>, and the other side who will=C2=A0<em>pay to take on emis=
sions</em>, and you =E2=80=94=C2=A0the ESG Consultant But Evil who arranges=
 the trade =E2=80=94=C2=A0take a fee from both sides.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I feel like if you play your cards right you c=
ould find a few counterparties like that in Texas? It is not=C2=A0<em>quite=
=C2=A0</em>the case that Texas has an alternative carbon-emissions accounti=
ng regime in which companies are penalized for not emitting enough carbon. =
But it is=C2=A0<em>a little bit=C2=A0</em>the case. Right now big financial=
 firms=C2=A0<em>are=C2=A0</em><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusines=
s.com/click/29707590.273527/aHR0cHM6Ly9jb21wdHJvbGxlci50ZXhhcy5nb3YvYWJvdXQ=
vbWVkaWEtY2VudGVyL25ld3MvMjAyMjA4MjQtdGV4YXMtY29tcHRyb2xsZXItZ2xlbm4taGVnYX=
ItYW5ub3VuY2VzLWxpc3Qtb2YtZmluYW5jaWFsLWNvbXBhbmllcy10aGF0LWJveWNvdHQtZW5lc=
md5LWNvbXBhbmllcy0xNjYxMjY3ODE1MDk5/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfdab38c6" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">facing financial penalties in Texas</a> for not doing enough fossil-fue=
l financing. Set up a Texas shell company, have it buy all the worst fossil=
-fuel projects from all the ESG-sensitive companies around the world, have =
it produce=C2=A0insane amounts of carbon emissions, and then go to banks to=
 be like =E2=80=9Cif you lend=C2=A0<em>this=C2=A0</em>company money then yo=
u will get a ton of credit in Texas for fossil-fuel fifinancing.=E2=80=9D I=
 have not worked this idea out fully. But I bet someone will.</p>
